name: Matt Tolman
description: Matt Tolman is a member of the Game Artisans of Canada (www.gameartisans.ca). He has been an avid gamer his whole life and started designing games in 2007. He lives/designs games in Calgary, Alberta, and can be found at most board game nights at The Sentry Box, his favourite FLGS. He also attends Fallcon (www.fallcon.com), The Gathering of Friends, and the Spiele in Essen, Germany. His name is pronounced "Mat toll-man" Matt is a huge fan of BGG, and frequently shares his game designing exploits with the community. Most notably his game design diary for Undermining, and his prototyping how-to videos, where he sheds some light on his process.
